==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Many-sided
<hw>Ma"ny-sid`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having many sides; -- said of figures. Hence, presenting many
questions or subjects for consideration; <as>as, a <ex>many-sided</ex>
topic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Interested in, and having an aptitude for, many
unlike pursuits or objects of attention; versatile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ma"ny-sid`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 894 --></p>

<p><ent>manywise</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>manyways</ent>⟦br⟧
